data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":199,"item_id":"msg_0a99deb098718b2200693a220708488195b660942559a4316f","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a detailed Whistleblower Policy aimed at ensuring a transparent and safe working environment. The policy encourages employees to report any unethical or illegal activities they witness. Here are key aspects:\n\n- **Who can report:** The policy applies to all employees, contractors, and third parties.\n- **Definition:** A whistleblower is someone who reports activities that are illegal, unethical, or otherwise not in accordance with company policy.\n- **Reporting procedures:** Employees can report issues by contacting the Human Resources Department, emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com, or calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212.\n- **Retaliation prohibition:** Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited, with disciplinary actions for those who retaliate.\n- **Confidentiality:** The identity of the whistleblower will be kept confidential as permitted by law.\n- **Investigation:** All reports will be promptly and thoroughly investigated.","logprobs":[]}

